The paper proposes a formal model of distributed computing based on register automata, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The model is also related to logic, specifically first-order logic on graphs and partial fixpoint logic, which suggests that it could be categorized under Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The use of finite-state controllers and registers to represent local memory of processes also relates to Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the expressive power of the model, which could be categorized under Programming Languages (cs.PL). Finally, the model captures synchronous network algorithms, which falls under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
